    section.home-about-area
      .container
        .row.align-items-center.justify-content-between
          .col-lg-6.col-md-6.home-about-left
            img.img-fluid.img-thumbnail.rounded-circle[src="img/janet_j3.jpg" alt="Me and my little niece" title="Me and my little niece"]
          .col-lg-5.col-md-6.home-about-right
            h1.text-uppercase
              | Janet's Urgent GRS Surgery Fund
            p
              | I’m going to say something that I rarely do: I need help.
              b
                | &nbsp;I need your help to cover the cost of life-altering surgery
              | . I have been suﬀering, and for the longest time, I couldn’t communicate that to the people closest to me. This pain kept me from experiencing things in my youth, it caused tremendous strain on my family, and
              b
                | &nbsp;it nearly cost me my life
              | . Some days are better than others, but now, more than ever, I need help. I need treatment. One simple surgery will allow me to live a happy, healthy life. I’ve already been living as a woman for 7+ years, I have gone into medical debt to help cover the costs of specialists, medical testing and therapy, and have jumped through every hoop the government forces me to jump through. But I can’t aﬀord this life-saving medical procedure and insurance will not cover any cost.
              br
              br
              | <b>I want to give you something back!</b> (details below.)
            h2
              | Goal:
              span[style="color: green"]
                | &nbsp;$9700
            a.btn.btn-primary.text-uppercase[href="#"]
              | Make a Donation
          .col-lg-12.pt-60.the-story
            .title.text-center
              h1.mb-10
                | The Story
            p
              blockquote
                | ... to go to the gym not fear being chased down by a security guard ...
            p
              | I am asking for your help in raising $9,700 to cover the cost of surgery
              | &nbsp; that will allow me to be happy in my own skin; to get off carcinogenic androgen blockers, to not fear walking into a bathroom and being chased down by a security guard; to not be stopped and frisked at every airport; to simply just exist.
            p
              | Currently, I work full-time and do charity and volunteer work. I live paycheck to paycheck juggling medical bills and will end up taking out a loan to cover any costs not raised here for the surgery. My doctors, both medical specialists, and therapist agree that
              b
                | &nbsp;this surgical treatment is life-altering and will lead to a better quality of life.
            p
              | My goal is to raise $1,000 as soon as possible
              | &nbsp;to schedule the pre-payment needed to reserve a surgical date with Dr. Kaushik. The sooner the better. The remainder will cover the cost of surgery that need to be paid up-front before the date (
              b
                | April 2019 or June 2019
              | ). With this current national and international political climate, I greatly fear these treatments will not be available in the near future and am determined, more than ever, to get this done. I cannot wait anymore.
            p
              | First and foremost, I wouldn’t be alive if it weren’t for the support of friends and family.
              b
                | &nbsp;I also would not be able to have gotten this far in this process without the support of my community and I am so grateful and appreciative that you are considering sharing this page or donating to it.
              b
                | &nbsp;Any donation is helpful, great or small. To help me get the word out please consider sharing this page to your Facebook Timeline!
            p
              b
                | &nbsp;I can’t do this without your help! If you consider yourself an ally, please consider this as an opportunity to give back to a community that is often under-served!
            p
              | For a donation of <b>$10</b> or more I will write you and mail a personal letter of thanks.
              br
              | For <b>$25</b> or more I'll do it on a hand painted card.
              br
              |  For <b>$150</b> I'll do the above AND and a hand crocheted scarf or hat.
              br
              |  or <b>$750</b> I'll paint a portrait of you or your favorite subject in acrylic and send it
              br
              |  &nbsp;to you.
            p
              | Please give anything you can! Even a $1 donation helps, sharing this on social media can help even more! Prayers are appreciated too. Thank you for your support!
            p
              | What your donation
              b
                | &nbsp;WILL
              | &nbsp;go towards:
              ul
                li
                  |  - The actual cost of the procedure
                li
                  |  - Expenses for travelling directly related to the procedure (such as plane tickets/ acquisition of a passport)
                li
                  |  - Expenses for after care
            p
              |  What your donation
              b
                | &nbsp;WILL NOT
              | &nbsp;go towards:
              ul
                li
                  |  - Any personal expenses of mine that are not directly related to this procedure
              br
